description.plain:
The Beatnuts is a hip-hop group and production duo comprised of Queens, New York natives Psycho Les and JuJu. While Les and JuJu began producing together in 1990, the group began as a trio with rapper Fashion a.k.a. Al' Tariq, but he left the group to go solo after the release of their debut EP Intoxicated Demons (1993) and their first full-length album The Beatnuts: Street Level (1994).

The Beatnuts went on to release the hit singles “Watch Out Now” and “Off the Books” with Big Pun and Cuban Link—both charting on the Billboard Hot 100. They have also produced tracks for Common, Akon, Capone-N-Noreaga, Fat Joe, and Ice-T among others.

description.plain:
One of the Beatnuts' first commercial hits, taken from their 1999 album Musical Massacre.

The Latin-tinged beat samples “Hi-Jack” by Enoch Light. The sample was part of a controversy involving Jennifer Lopez’s “Jenny From The Block,” which used the same sample and sounded similar to “Watch Out Now”.

The ‘Nuts, having been angered over the artist and The Trackmasters & Cory Rooney, released a response to “Jenny From The Block” with “Confused Rappers” in 2004. After recieving royalties from the song, Ju-Ju ended the feud, but Psycho Les still harbors dislike for The Trackmasters.

“Props Over Here” was intended to be the radio-friendly single the Beatnuts first LP. It is more accessible and laid back than most of the songs on the album and samples “Wee Tina” by Donald Byrd & Booker Little and “Upon This Rock” by Joe Farrell.

It was released as the first single from The Beatnuts' debut album and went to #39 on the US Rap Chart and #10 on the US Dance Chart in the summer of 1994.
